y(d,"func:readAllRelatedRecords");
s("name","readAllRelatedRecords");
s(o,"Given a passed in set of equipment records:\n    1. Go through the relationship table and recursively include all other related records into the resulting\n       set. Ie. If the passed in records only contain an equipment that is referenced in a targetRef field, the corresponding record\n       from the sourceRef relationship will also be returned. The sourceRef relationships will also then be included recursively.\n       This ensures that both source and target records in a relationship will always be present in the resulting set.\n    2. Find all the records linked to the passed in set via the known \"refTag\" fields that are used to create relationships:\n         Supplies: ahuRef, chillerPlantRef, chilledWaterPlantRef, boilerPlantRef\n         Contains: equipRef\n       Note, the code in SkySparkModelAggregator/SkySparkAssetInputMapper.cs must match the above definitions\n\nExample: readAllRelatedRecords(readAll(ahu))");
