y(d,"func:bacnetWritePropertyMultiple");
s("name","bacnetWritePropertyMultiple");
s(o,"Write properties for multiple BACnet objects. If the device supports\nthe WritePropertyMultiple service, then it will be used. Otherwise,\neach property will be written one-at-a-time.\n\nParameters\n - conn: the BACnet connection used to query the object properties\n - objPropDict: a Dict where the keys are the BACnet object identifiers\n to write. The value for each object identifier is a Dict containing\n the properties to write. This Dict is called a 'write specification'.\n The keys of the write specification Dict are the properties to write\n The value for each key of the write specification is a list with the format\n '[propVal, arrayIndex, priority]'. The arrayIndex and priority are optional.\n\n Returns a grid in the same format as `bacnetWriteObjectProperty`\n\n Examples:\n   // Write present value and object name for 2 objects\n   bacnetWritePropertyMultiple(@connRef, {av1:{present_value:[100], object_name:[\"foo\"]},\n                                          av2:{present_value:[20, null, 8], object_name:[\"bar\"]}})\n");
