y(d,"func:refrigValveSignalOscillationFreq");
s("dis","Refrigerant Valve Position Oscillating Control Signals");
s("ruleOn","point and cmd and kind==\"Number\" and refrig and valve");
s("help","Control signal is continuously oscillating or hunting for Refrigerant Valve Position Command when the difference between min and max value of control signal is more than 80% (adj.)  in 5 mins (adj.) window.\n\nThe above conditions to remain true continuously for >30mins (adj.) (ie. 6 continuous cycles/windows of 5 mins)  2 (adj.) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj.) (ie. 12 continuous cycles/windows of 5 mins) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\n  Recommendations:\n  1. Check and perform PID tuning.\n  2. Check for loose connection in control signal cable/wire.\n  3. Check for any faults in controller terminal or field device.\n  4. Check the sensor that is controlling the signal for any faults.\n  5. Validate the control logic software in controller.\n");
s("name","refrigValveSignalOscillationFreq");
s("help2","Control signal is continuously oscillating or hunting for Refrigerant Valve Position Command when the difference between min and max value of control signal is more than 80% (adj.)  in 5 mins (adj.) window.\n\nThe above conditions to remain true continuously for >30mins (adj.) (ie. 6 continuous cycles/windows of 5 mins)  2 (adj.) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj.) (ie. 12 continuous cycles/windows of 5 mins) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\n  Recommendations:\n  1. Check and perform PID tuning.\n  2. Check for loose connection in control signal cable/wire.\n  3. Check for any faults in controller terminal or field device.\n  4. Check the sensor that is controlling the signal for any faults.\n  5. Validate the control logic software in controller.\n");
