y(d,"func:bacnetReadObject");
s("name","bacnetReadObject");
s(o,"Read properties for a BACnet object.\n\nParameters:\n - conn: the BACnet connector to use for reading objects.\n - obj: the BACnet object to read. Can be any type resolvable using\n `toRec`. The value should resolve to a point record that has a `bacnetCur`\n tag. You may also pass any Str that is a valid value for the `bacnetCur` tag.\n Finally, you may pass null or the connector record itself to read the Device object\n corresponding to the BACnet connector.\n - props: The property, or list of properties to read. If omitted, a default\n set of properties will be read. A property may be identified by either its\n numeric property identifier, or the property name (case-insensitive). If you\n want to read a specific element of an array, then given give a Dict like\n this: '{property_name, i:index}'\n\nReturns a grid with the following columns:\n - objectId: A Str representation of the object identifier\n - propertyId: The property identifier\n - propertyName: The property name\n - value: the property's value\n\nExamples:\n  // Get the default set of properties\n  bacnetReadObject(conn, \"AV1\")\n\n  // Both these examples get the Object_Name\n  bacnetReadObject(conn, \"AV1\", \"object_name\")\n  bacnetReadObject(conn, \"AV1\", 77)\n\n  // Get the Present_Value, and Out_Of_Service values\n  bacnetReadObject(conn, \"AV1\", [85, \"out_of_service\"])\n");
