y(d,"func:analogDamperMismatchExhaust");
s("dis","Exhaust Air Damper command & feedback mismatch");
s("ruleOn","equip and ahu and exhaustAir");
s("help","Exhaust air damper command and status is not matching for 2-position dampers or difference between damper command and feedback is more than 10(adj) for modulating dampers.\nThe above conditions to remain true for >30mins (adj) 2 (adj) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check damper command terminals in controller/DDC panel for any faults. Check for command cable damage/break.\n2. Check damper command relay for any faults (2-position damper). Check damper command output voltage signal (modulating damper).\n3. Check damper actuator for any faults (both command and feedback terminals). Verify voltage signal/power supply and settings in the actuator.\n4. Ensure actuator-damper shaft coupling is intact.\n5. Check for any mechanical faults in damper.\n6. Check damper feedback terminals in controller/DDC panel for any faults. Check for feedback cable damage/break.");
s("name","analogDamperMismatchExhaust");
s("help2","Exhaust air damper command and status is not matching for 2-position dampers or difference between damper command and feedback is more than 10(adj) for modulating dampers.\nThe above conditions to remain true for >30mins (adj) 2 (adj) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check damper command terminals in controller/DDC panel for any faults. Check for command cable damage/break.\n2. Check damper command relay for any faults (2-position damper). Check damper command output voltage signal (modulating damper).\n3. Check damper actuator for any faults (both command and feedback terminals). Verify voltage signal/power supply and settings in the actuator.\n4. Ensure actuator-damper shaft coupling is intact.\n5. Check for any mechanical faults in damper.\n6. Check damper feedback terminals in controller/DDC panel for any faults. Check for feedback cable damage/break.");
