y(d,"func:ruleOrphans");
s("name","ruleOrphans");
s(o,"Search the database for all previously cached sparks and KPIs which no\nlonger have a valid rule record.  The targets parameter may be any expr\naccepted by `toRecList()` or null for all.  Span is any expr accepted\nby `toSpan()`.  This situation occurs when you delete rule records from\nthe database which have already cached their results.\n\nThe result is a grid with a row for each unique target+rule combination.\nThe grid has following columns:\n  - targetRef: target id\n  - ruleRef: orphaned rule id\n  - ruleType: \"spark\" or \"kpi\"\n  - numDates: number of dates with orphaned sparks or kpis\n\nYou may pipe the results of this function directly to `ruleDelete()`\nto delete the orphaned data.\n\nAlso see the [documentation]`ext-rule::doc#orphans`.\n\nExamples:\n  // run narrow report on specific targets and span\n  readAll(ahu).ruleOrphans(thisMonth)\n\n  // report on all orphaned data across database\n  ruleOrphans(null, null)\n\n  // delete all orphans across all targets and all time\n  ruleOrphans(null, null).ruleDelete\n");
