y(d,"func:renameTags");
s("name","renameTags");
s(o,"Rename a set of tags on a list of records or across the entire project\ndatabase.  This function is easily paired with `deprecatedTags()` to\npreview and fix standard tags which are deprecated over time.\n\nThe recs parameters specify the recs for the operation.  Or pass\nnull to rename every rec in the project database.\n\nThe renames parameter may be any of the following shapes:\n  - Dict of old to new tag names\n  - Grid with 'old' and 'new' columns\n\nIf the new value is a string, then the tag is renamed to the given\nnew name.  If new value is the Remove value then the tag is simply\nremoved (only if removeOld option passed).  If the new value is\na conjuct formatted as \"foo-bar-baz\", then each part is created\nas a marker tag.\n\nSummary of options:\n  - commit: marker to force commit (preview by default)\n  - removeOld: remove the old tag (old tag left by default)\n  - limit: number of diffs (defaults to 1000)\n\nThe default behavior is to preview the changes only and to leave\nthe old tags in place side-by-side with the new tags.  To apply\nthe changes pass the 'commit' option.  To force removal of the\nold tags pass the 'removeOld'.\n\nAs a saftey measure no more than 1000 diffs are previewed or\ncommitted.  You can remove the limit by passing '-limit' in the\noptions.  However if removing the limit in a large project, then\nboth thew preview or commit results might be too large to view in\nthe Shell view.  In this case, pipe the results to a file\nusing `ioWriteZinc()`.\n\nExamples:\n  // rename of foo -> bar across all records\n  // opts: preview, leave old tag, limit 1000\n  renameTags(null, {foo: \"bar\"})\n\n  // rename of foo -> bar across all records\n  // opts: commit, remove old tag, no limit\n  renameTags(null, {foo: \"bar\"}, {commit, removeOld, -limit})\n\n  // remove of foo across all points\n  // opts: preview, remove old tag, limit 10\n  readAll(point).renameTags({-foo}, {removeOld, limit:10})\n\n  // rename of elecMeter -> elec + meter and steamPlant -> steam + plant\n  // across all equip records\n  readAll(equip).renameTags({elecMeter: \"elec-meter\", steamPlant: \"steam-plant\"})\n\n  // combine with deprecatedTags() to rename all deprecated tags\n  // and pipe results to a zinc file in the io/ directory\n  renameTags(null, deprecatedTags()).ioWriteZinc(`io/rename-log.zinc`)\n");
