s("help","VAV zone temp is more than setpoint by 5°C (adj.) when damper is open and AHU Status is On in occupied mode.\nAssociated AHU discharge temperature is satisfied.\nThe above conditions were true for >60mins (adj.) (2 times or more in a day) or >120mins (adj.) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check VAV box damper manual overrides on front end.\n2. Verify VAV box damper point characteristics/configurations in controller & actuator voltage/power.\n3. Check if VAV box damper is physically stuck.\n4. Check sensor location or any external influence (Infiltration/Exfiltration).\n5. Check if AHU DA temperature setpoint is set as per design.\n6. Check if AHU duct static pressure setpoint is set as per design.");
