y(d,"func:navResolve");
s("name","navResolve");
s(o,"Resolve a list of navigation Refs to a list of Dict records.\nAlso see `docFresco::Nav#navSelAny`.\n\nDefault behavior is to resolve using only the local project.  Pass\nthe 'navCluster' marker option to resolve across the cluster based\non the [projIncludeFilter]`docFresco::Nav#projIncludeFilter`\nconfiguration.\n\nNavigation [nesting]`docFresco::Nav#nesting` is when a given level\nof the tree is organized using a reference tag.  For example 'equip'\nrecs are nested by the 'equipRef' tag.  The default behavior of\nthis method is to **not** apply nesting to compute children of\nof a navigation ref.  However this behavior can be overridden by\npassing the 'nestExpand' marker tag.  This option is *extremely*\nexpensive and should be avoided if at all possible (especially if\ncombined with 'navCluster' option).  Examples:\n\n  // nested tree of equip via equipRef\n  eq\n    eqA\n      eqA1\n      eqA2\n    eqB\n\n  // default yields only [eq]\n  navRef(\"equip\", eq).navResolve\n\n  // yields [eq, eqA, eqA1, eqA2, eqB] (eq and its nested children)\n  navRef(\"equip\", eq).navResolve({nestExpand})\n\nNote the nestExpand feature only works at the leaf level.  In the\nexample above the target name is \"equip\", so we can expand 'eq' to\ninclude its nested children.  However if target was \"point\", then we\nwould **not** expand 'eq' to include the points from 'eqA', 'eqA1', 'eqA2',\nand 'eqB'.\n\nOption summary:\n  - 'kind': pass in kind value string used in input\n  - 'navCluster': pass marker to resolve across cluster\n  - 'nestExpand': pass marker to expand nested children (equip via equipRef)\n  - 'itself':  pass marker to resolve selection itself (not descendent targets);\n    the behavior of this function with ancestors/groups is subject to change\n");
s("code","R_61");
y(d,"func:lowdeltaTboilerOn");
s("dis","Boiler operating when HW loop Delta - T is low");
s("ruleOn","equip and boilerPlant");
s("param","(_,_,/*threshold:*/5,/*minTime:*/30min,/*maxTime:*/60min,/*supplytempMinVal:*/25,/*supplytempMaxVal:*/90,/*returntempMinVal:*/25,/*returntempMaxVal:*/90,/*freq:*/2,/*ruleWorkOrder:*/\"None\",/*priority:*/\"Medium\",/*type:*/\"Energy\")");
s("param2","(_,_,/*threshold:*/10,/*minTime:*/30min,/*maxTime:*/60min,/*supplytempMinVal:*/77,/*supplytempMaxVal:*/194,/*returntempMinVal:*/77,/*returntempMaxVal:*/194,/*freq:*/2,/*ruleWorkOrder:*/\"None\",/*priority:*/\"Medium\",/*type:*/\"Energy\")");
s("help","Boiler is On when difference between common/header HW supply and return temp is less than 5 degC (adj).\nThe above conditions were true for >30mins (adj) 2 (adj) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Validate HW system enable logic at low deltaT.\n2. Check for any boiler command manual overrides at chiller local panel or at front end.\n3. Check boiler command relay for any faults.\n4. Check boiler status sensor for any faults.\n5. Verify boiler internal controls.");
s("name","lowdeltaTboilerOn");
s("help2","Boiler is On when difference between common/header HW supply and return temp is less than 10°F (adj). The above conditions were true for >30mins (adj) 2 (adj) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Validate HW system enable logic at low deltaT.\n2. Check for any boiler command manual overrides at chiller local panel or at front end.\n3. Check boiler command relay for any faults.\n4. Check boiler status sensor for any faults.\n5. Verify boiler internal controls.");
