s("help2","AHU return duct flow is lower than setpoint by 10% (adj) of setpoint and return fan speed is greater than 85% (adj).\nThe above conditions to remain true for >30mins (adj) 2 (adj) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check if AHU return fan speed command is overridden between 85% and 100% on front end.\n2. Check for any mechanical issues/faults in return fan motor/VSD.\n3. Validate AHU return fan speed control logic in controller to ensure fan speed is commanded to 100% (max speed).\n4. Verify fan speed control design, return duct flow setpoint, return duct flow sensor location.");
