y(d,"func:diffuserSignalOscillationFreq");
s("dis","Diffuser Position Oscillating Control Signals");
s("ruleOn","point and cmd and kind==\"Number\" and diffuser");
s("help","Control signal is continuously oscillating or hunting for Diffuser Position Command when the difference between min and max value of control signal is more than 80% (adj.)  in 5 mins (adj.) window.\n\nThe above conditions to remain true continuously for >30mins (adj.) (ie. 6 continuous cycles/windows of 5 mins)  2 (adj.) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj.) (ie. 12 continuous cycles/windows of 5 mins) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\n  Recommendations:\n  1. Check and perform PID tuning.\n  2. Check for loose connection in control signal cable/wire.\n  3. Check for any faults in controller terminal or field device.\n  4. Check the sensor that is controlling the signal for any faults.\n  5. Validate the control logic software in controller.\n");
s("name","diffuserSignalOscillationFreq");
s("help2","Control signal is continuously oscillating or hunting for Diffuser Position Command when the difference between min and max value of control signal is more than 80% (adj.)  in 5 mins (adj.) window.\n\nThe above conditions to remain true continuously for >30mins (adj.) (ie. 6 continuous cycles/windows of 5 mins)  2 (adj.) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj.) (ie. 12 continuous cycles/windows of 5 mins) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\n  Recommendations:\n  1. Check and perform PID tuning.\n  2. Check for loose connection in control signal cable/wire.\n  3. Check for any faults in controller terminal or field device.\n  4. Check the sensor that is controlling the signal for any faults.\n  5. Validate the control logic software in controller.\n");
y(d,"func:hisPeriodUnion");
s("name","hisPeriodUnion");
s(o,"Find the union of two or more historical periods. The 'periods'\nparameter may be:\n  - Grid?: a single grid where the first column is a \"ts\" column,\n  and all remaining columns are named anything and contain period values.\n  - Grid?[]: a list of grids where each grid has the format described above,\n\nAll input grids must be [normalized]`hisPeriodNormalize()`\n\nThe resulting grid has \"ts\" and \"v0\" column, where \"v0\" is duration in hours.\n\nExample:\n  // find periods when either a, b, or c is on\n  hisPeriodUnion([a, b, c])\n");
