y(d,"func:snmpReadTable");
s("name","snmpReadTable");
s(o,"Synchronously read an SNMP table and return it as a Grid.\n\nParams:\n - conn: the SNMP connector to read against.\n - table: the qname of the table to read (e.g. '\"SNMPv2-MIB::sysORTable\"').\n\nEach column's metadata includes tag 'snmpColIdentity' which is the OID of\nthe column object-type in the MIB.  In addition to the columns\nspecified in the MIB, each row will have a column 'snmpRowIndex'.\nThis value is the common OID suffix for each cell in the row. In other words,\nit represents the row index. Each table cell's OID is therefore:\n\n  col.meta[\"snmpColIdentity\"] + \".\" + row[\"snmpRowIndex\"]\n\nExamples:\n\n  grid = read(snmpConn and dis==\"SNMP Demo\").snmpReadTable(\"SNMPv2-MIB::sysORTable\")\n\n**NOTE: this function is incubating and subject to change.**\n");
