y(d,"func:userCommit");
s("name","userCommit");
s(o,"Commit one or more diffs to the user database.\nThe argument may be one of the following:\n  - result of `diff()`\n  - list of `diff()` to commit multiple diffs at once\n\nIf one diff is passed, return the new record. If a list\nof diffs is passed, return a list of new records.\n\nWhen creating a new user the following tags must be specified:\n - `id` - Must be '@<username>'\n - `user`\n - `username` - Must match the 'id'.\n - `tz`\n - `userRole`\n\nIf the `userAuth` tag is not specified, a \"dummy\" SCRAM configuration will be\nbe generated, but the user will **not** be able to log in until a password\nis set. This can be done in Axon using `userSetPassword()`. Otherwise, you\nwill need to reset their password in the user manager, or if email reset is\nenabled the user can do it from the login page using the forgot my password feature.\n\nExamples:\npre>\n// add a new user\nuserTags: {id:@bach, user, username:\"bach\", userRole:\"op\", tz:\"New_York\"}\nnewRec: commit(diff(null, userTags, {add}))\n\n// update the appAccess tag on all operator users\nuserReadAll(user and userRole==\"op\")\n  .toRecList\n  .map(r => diff(r, {appAccess:\"energy,his\"}))\n  .userCommit\n\n// remove all disabled users\nuserReadAll(user and disabled)\n  .toRecList\n  .map(r => diff(r, null, {remove}))\n  .userCommit\n<pre\n");
