y(d,"func:mlSvm");
s("name","mlSvm");
s(o,"Create a Support Vector Machine (SVM) for classification. The SVM\ncan be configured for either binary or multiclass classification.\n\n  - kernel: The kernel function\n  - k: The number of classes\n  - opts: A Dict containing the configuration options for the SVM. The\n  following options are supported for both binary and multiclass SVMs:\n    - c: (Number) The soft-margin penalty parameter (default 1.0).\n    - tol: (Number) The tolerance of convergence/termination criteria (default 0.001)\n\n    The following options can be used to configure a **Binary** SVM:\n    - cn: (Number) The soft-margin penalty parameter for negative instances (default: cp)\n\n    The following options can be used to configure a **Multiclass** SVM:\n    - strategy: (Str) the classification strategy to use. Supported values\n      are 'one_vs_one' and 'one_vs_all'. (default: 'one_vs_one')\n\nNote: for a binary SVM (k=2) when you create the training data you must map\nall results to either '-1' or '1'.\n");
