s("help","AHU enthalpy wheel is running when outside air enthalpy is less than return air enthalpy/exhaust air enthalpy by 4°C (adj.) and zone temp is greater than setpoint by 3°C  (adj.)/discharge temp is greater than setpoint by 2°C  (adj.) or enthalpy wheel is running when outside air enthalpy is greater than return air enthalpy/exhaust air enthalpy by 4°C (adj and zone temp is less than setpoint by 3°C  (adj.)/discharge temp is less than setpoint by  2°C  (adj.).\nThe above conditions to remain true for >30mins (adj) 2 (adj) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Verify Enthalpy wheel operation logic in controller.\n2. Check for Enthalpy wheel manual overrides on front end/local panel.\n3. Check Enthalpy wheel status sensor faults.\n4. Check Enthalpy wheel command relay faults.");
