y(d,"func:ruleSparkExplain");
s("name","ruleSparkExplain");
s(o,"Return explanation information for a spark.  The param must be a\nspark dict - typically a row from the `ruleSparks()` function.\n\nThe explanation result is a dict with following tags:\n - spark: the spark dict parameter\n - explain: fandoc string taken from 'explain' tag on the spark if available\n - help: the fandoc string for rule help tag\n - points: Ref[] for points used as inputs for the spark\n - tuning: Dict of tuning parameters\n\nIf the spark itself defines a 'points' tag with a Ref[] value, then it\nis used.  Otherwise, the system will attempt to resolve point inputs\nfrom the rule's component input bindings.\n\nIf the spark defines a 'tuning' tag, then it is used.  Otherwise, the\nsystem will include the current tuning parameters.  Note that it is\npossible that tuning tags have been modified since the spark was computed.\nSo the tuning Dict included by this function may not reflect the tuning\nactually used.\n\nThis function is used by the Explain action in the Spark|Equip view.\nOverride this function to provide customized explain information.  Each\ntag in the explain dict is displayed in the UI as follows:\n  - dicts are shown using an info icon popup\n  - multi-line strings are shown as fandoc\n  - all other values are shown using their string value\n\nExample:\n  spark: ruleSparks(null, lastWeek, null).first\n  ruleSparkExplain(spark)\n");
