s("help2","AHU outside air flow is less than setpoint by 10% (adj.) of flow setpoint and outside air damper is above 10% (adj.).\nThe above conditions to remain true for >30mins (adj.) 2 (adj.) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj.) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check if AHU Outside air damper command is overridden to a position between 10% and 100% on front end.\n2. Check if outside air damper is physically stuck. Check for any mechanical issues/faults in actuator, damper.\n3. Check and verify the voltage signals from controller to outside air damper actuator.\n4. Validate AHU outside air flow control logic in controller to ensure outside air damper is commanded to 100% (max position).");
