y(d,"func:mixedDamperSignalOscillationFreq");
s("dis","Mixed Air Damper Position Oscillating Control Signals");
s("ruleOn","point and cmd and kind==\"Number\" and mixed and damper");
s("help","Control signal is continuously oscillating or hunting for Mixed Air Damper Command when the difference between min and max value of control signal is more than 80% (adj.)  in 5 mins (adj.) window.\n\nThe above conditions to remain true continuously for >30mins (adj.) (ie. 6 continuous cycles/windows of 5 mins)  2 (adj.) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj.) (ie. 12 continuous cycles/windows of 5 mins) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\n  Recommendations:\n  1. Check and perform PID tuning.\n  2. Check for loose connection in control signal cable/wire.\n  3. Check for any faults in controller terminal or field device.\n  4. Check the sensor that is controlling the signal for any faults.\n  5. Validate the control logic software in controller.\n");
s("name","mixedDamperSignalOscillationFreq");
s("help2","Control signal is continuously oscillating or hunting for Mixed Air Damper Command when the difference between min and max value of control signal is more than 80% (adj.)  in 5 mins (adj.) window.\n\nThe above conditions to remain true continuously for >30mins (adj.) (ie. 6 continuous cycles/windows of 5 mins)  2 (adj.) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj.) (ie. 12 continuous cycles/windows of 5 mins) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\n  Recommendations:\n  1. Check and perform PID tuning.\n  2. Check for loose connection in control signal cable/wire.\n  3. Check for any faults in controller terminal or field device.\n  4. Check the sensor that is controlling the signal for any faults.\n  5. Validate the control logic software in controller.\n");
s("code","R_197");
y(d,"func:vavZoneColdCoolOnly_MinDmpPD");
s("dis","VAV Zone Cold when damper at min position - Cooling only");
s("help","VAV zone temp is less than setpoint by 5°C (adj.) when damper is at minimum position and AHU Status is On in occupied mode.\nAssociated AHU discharge temperature is satisfied.\nThe above conditions were true for >60mins (adj.) (2 times or more in a day) or >120mins (adj.) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check if damper is physically stuck or manually overridden on front end.\n2. Check if damper is at design minimum position.\n3. Verify VAV box damper point characteristics/configurations in controller & actuator voltage/power.\n4. Check sensor location or any external influence (Infiltration/Exfiltration).\n5. Verify zone temp SP, AHU duct static pressure SP, AHU discharge temp SP) is as per design.");
s("name","vavZoneColdCoolOnly_MinDmpPD");
s("help2","VAV zone temp is less than setpoint by 5°F (adj.) when damper is at minimum position and AHU Status is On in occupied mode. Associated AHU discharge temperature is satisfied. The above conditions were true for >60mins (adj.) (2 times or more in a day) or >120mins (adj.) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check if damper is physically stuck or manually overridden on front end.\n2. Check if damper is at design minimum position.\n3. Verify VAV box damper point characteristics/configurations in controller & actuator voltage/power.\n4. Check sensor location or any external influence (Infiltration/Exfiltration).\n5. Verify zone temp SP, AHU duct static pressure SP, AHU discharge temp SP) is as per design.");
