s("dis","VAV Zone Hot when damper open & Reheat OFF");
s("param","(_,_,/*tempdeviation:*/5,/*dischargeTempThreshold:*/2,/*minTime:*/60min,/*reheatValveThreshold:*/5,/*damperThreshold:*/20,/*maxTime:*/120min,/*freq:*/2,/*znTmpLowLimit:*/10,/*znTmpHighLimit:*/35,/*znTmpspLowLimit:*/18,/*znTmpspHighLimit:*/28,/*ruleWorkOrder:*/\"None\",/*priority:*/\"Low\",/*type:*/\"Comfort\")");
s("param2","(_,_,/*tempdeviation:*/5,/*dischargeTempThreshold:*/3,/*minTime:*/60min,/*reheatValveThreshold:*/5,/*damperThreshold:*/20,/*maxTime:*/120min,/*freq:*/2,/*znTmpLowLimit:*/50,/*znTmpHighLimit:*/95,/*znTmpspLowLimit:*/64,/*znTmpspHighLimit:*/82,/*ruleWorkOrder:*/\"None\",/*priority:*/\"Low\",/*type:*/\"Comfort\")");
s("help","VAV zone temp is more than setpoint by 5°C (adj.) when damper is open and Reheat valve is close i.e.<5% or all Reheat stages are Off and AHU Status is On in occupied mode.\nAssociated AHU discharge temperature is satisfied.\nThe above conditions were true for >60mins (adj.) (2 times or more in a day) or >120mins (adj.) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check VAV box damper manual overrides on front end.\n2. Verify VAV box damper point characteristics/configurations in controller & actuator voltage/power.\n3. Check if VAV box damper is physically stuck.\n4. Check sensor location or any external influence (Infiltration/Exfiltration).\n5. Check if Reheat Valve/Stage Relay is stuck open/on.\n6. Check if AHU DA temperature setpoint is set as per design.\n7. Check if AHU duct static pressure setpoint is set as per design.");
s("name","vavZoneHotRhtOff_MaxDmpPD");
s("help2","VAV zone temp is more than setpoint by 5°F (adj.) when damper is open and Reheat valve is close i.e.<5% or all Reheat stages are Off and AHU Status is On in occupied mode. Associated AHU discharge temperature is satisfied. The above conditions were true for >60mins (adj.) (2 times or more in a day) or >120mins (adj.) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check VAV box damper manual overrides on front end.\n2. Verify VAV box damper point characteristics/configurations in controller & actuator voltage/power.\n3. Check if VAV box damper is physically stuck.\n4. Check sensor location or any external influence (Infiltration/Exfiltration).\n5. Check if Reheat Valve/Stage Relay is stuck open/on.\n6. Check if AHU DA temperature setpoint is set as per design.\n7. Check if AHU duct static pressure setpoint is set as per design.");
