y(d,"func:raPressureLessThanSPHighSpeed");
s("dis","RA Low Duct Static Pressure with fan speed > 85%");
s("help","AHU return duct static pressure is lower than setpoint by 20% (adj.) of setpoint and return fan speed is greater than 85% (adj.) when AHU return fan status is On.\nThe above conditions to remain true for >30mins (adj.) 2 (adj.) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj.) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check if AHU return fan speed command is overridden between 85% and 100% on front end.\n2. Check for any mechanical issues/faults in return fan motor/VSD.\n3. Validate AHU return fan speed control logic in controller to ensure fan speed is commanded to 100% (max speed).\n4. Verify fan speed control design, return duct pressure setpoint, return duct pressure sensor location.");
s("name","raPressureLessThanSPHighSpeed");
s("help2","AHU return duct static pressure is lower than setpoint by 20% (adj.) of setpoint and return fan speed is greater than 85% (adj.) when AHU return fan status is On.\nThe above conditions to remain true for >30mins (adj.) 2 (adj.) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj.) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check if AHU return fan speed command is overridden between 85% and 100% on front end.\n2. Check for any mechanical issues/faults in return fan motor/VSD.\n3. Validate AHU return fan speed control logic in controller to ensure fan speed is commanded to 100% (max speed).\n4. Verify fan speed control design, return duct pressure setpoint, return duct pressure sensor location.");
