y(d,"func:hexPriValveMismatch");
s("dis","HEX Primary Valve Command and Feedback Mismatch");
s("help","Difference between Heat Exchanger (HEX) primary valve command and feedback is more than 10%.\n\nThe above conditions to remain true for >30mins (adj) 2 (adj) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check if valve is physically stuck at some position.\n2. Check for valve actuator faults and verify its operation, power supply, wire terminations.\n3. Check for any blockages in valve stem movement.\n4. Check for faults, loose connections in command and feedback cables and controller terminals.\n5. Verify command and feedback point characteristics in controller.");
s("name","hexPriValveMismatch");
s("help2","Difference between Heat Exchanger (HEX) primary valve command and feedback is more than 10%.\n\nThe above conditions to remain true for >30mins (adj) 2 (adj) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check if valve is physically stuck at some position.\n2. Check for valve actuator faults and verify its operation, power supply, wire terminations.\n3. Check for any blockages in valve stem movement.\n4. Check for faults, loose connections in command and feedback cables and controller terminals.\n5. Verify command and feedback point characteristics in controller.");
