y(d,"func:bacnetLearn");
s("name","bacnetLearn");
s(o,"Deprecated - use `connLearn()`\n\nWalk the BACnet device to learn its points. The 'conn' parameter is\nthe BACnet connector record to use. The 'arg' parameter indicates which\nnode in the learn tree to return. Use 'null' to learn the root nodes\nTo delve deeper in the tree keep calling this function with value of\nthe \"learn\" column for the row you are interested in. If the resulting\ngrid does not have a \"learn\" column, then you have reached a leaf object -\nthat is, a point that can be added to the system.\n\nLearn the root levels of the tree:\npre>\nbacnetLearn(@myBacnetConn, null)\n\ndis           learn\n------------  -----\nANALOG_INPUT  0\nTREND_LOG     20\n<pre\nTo learn the 'ANALOG_INPUT' row, we call bacnetLearn again with the value\nof its learn column (i.e. '0'). The resulting grid does not have a learn\ncolumn so we have found a set of points we can add to the system.\npre>\nbacnetLearn(@myBacnetConn, 0)\n\nbacnetCur   dis            kind   point  unit\n---------   ---------      ----   -----  -----\nAI8         Ramp           Number ✓\nAI9         Temp           Number ✓\n<pre\n");
