y(d,"func:hbZoneHighCo2OADOpen");
s("dis","High CO2 for Wellness With OAD is open (Deprecated)");
s("help","AHU Zone/RA CO2 is higher than setpoint by 10% (adj) of CO2 setpoint and outside air damper is above 25% (adj).\nThe above conditions to remain true for >30mins (adj) 2 (adj) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check if AHU Outside air damper command is overridden to a position between 25% and 100% on front end.\n2. Check if outside air damper is physically stuck. Check for any mechanical issues/faults in actuator, damper.\n3. Check and verify the voltage signals from controller to outside air damper actuator.\n4. Validate AHU CO2 control logic in controller to ensure outside air damper is commanded to 100% (max position).\n5. Verify fresh air control design to ensure optimum fresh air intake for CO2 control in space, check sensor location.");
s("name","hbZoneHighCo2OADOpen");
s("help2","AHU Zone/RA CO2 is higher than setpoint by 10% (adj) of CO2 setpoint and outside air damper is above 25% (adj).\nThe above conditions to remain true for >30mins (adj) 2 (adj) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check if AHU Outside air damper command is overridden to a position between 25% and 100% on front end.\n2. Check if outside air damper is physically stuck. Check for any mechanical issues/faults in actuator, damper.\n3. Check and verify the voltage signals from controller to outside air damper actuator.\n4. Validate AHU CO2 control logic in controller to ensure outside air damper is commanded to 100% (max position).\n5. Verify fresh air control design to ensure optimum fresh air intake for CO2 control in space, check sensor location.");
