s("help","AHU sensible wheel is running when outside air temperature is less than return air temp/exhaust air temp by 4°C (adj.) and zone temp is greater than setpoint by 3°C (adj.)/discharge temp is greater than setpoint by 2°C (adj.) or sensible wheel is running when outside air temperature is greater than return air temp/exhaust air temp by 4°C (adj.) and zone temp is less than setpoint by 3°C (adj.)/discharge temp is less than setpoint by 2°C (adj.).\nThe above conditions to remain true for >30mins (adj) 2 (adj) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Verify Sensible wheel operation logic in controller.\n2. Check for Sensible wheel manual overrides on front end/local panel.\n3. Check Sensible wheel status sensor faults.\n4. Check Sensible wheel command relay faults.");
