s("dis","Chiller Manual Run");
s("ruleOn","equip and chiller and not cmdOnly and not statusOnly");
s("help","Chiller status is On and command is Off.\nThe above conditions were true for >30mins (adj) 2 (adj) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check for chiller command manual overrides at chiller local panel.\n2. Check chiller command relay for any faults.\n3. Check chiller status sensor for any faults.\n4. Verify chiller internal controls.");
s("name","chillerManualRun");
s("help2","Chiller status is On and command is Off.\nThe above conditions were true for >30mins (adj) 2 (adj) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check for chiller command manual overrides at chiller local panel.\n2. Check chiller command relay for any faults.\n3. Check chiller status sensor for any faults.\n4. Verify chiller internal controls.");
s("code","R_352");
y(d,"func:heatingValveSignalOscillationFreq");
s("dis","Heating Valve Position Oscillating Control Signals");
s("ruleOn","point and cmd and kind==\"Number\" and heating and valve");
s("help","Control signal is continuously oscillating or hunting for Heating Valve Position Command when the difference between min and max value of control signal is more than 80% (adj.)  in 5 mins (adj.) window.\n\nThe above conditions to remain true continuously for >30mins (adj.) (ie. 6 continuous cycles/windows of 5 mins)  2 (adj.) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj.) (ie. 12 continuous cycles/windows of 5 mins) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\n  Recommendations:\n  1. Check and perform PID tuning.\n  2. Check for loose connection in control signal cable/wire.\n  3. Check for any faults in controller terminal or field device.\n  4. Check the sensor that is controlling the signal for any faults.\n  5. Validate the control logic software in controller.\n");
s("name","heatingValveSignalOscillationFreq");
s("help2","Control signal is continuously oscillating or hunting for Heating Valve Position Command when the difference between min and max value of control signal is more than 80% (adj.)  in 5 mins (adj.) window.\n\nThe above conditions to remain true continuously for >30mins (adj.) (ie. 6 continuous cycles/windows of 5 mins)  2 (adj.) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj.) (ie. 12 continuous cycles/windows of 5 mins) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\n  Recommendations:\n  1. Check and perform PID tuning.\n  2. Check for loose connection in control signal cable/wire.\n  3. Check for any faults in controller terminal or field device.\n  4. Check the sensor that is controlling the signal for any faults.\n  5. Validate the control logic software in controller.\n");
