y(d,"func:raPressureHigherThanSPLowSpeed");
s("dis","RA High Duct Static Pressure with fan speed < 85%");
s("help","AHU return duct static pressure is higher than setpoint by 20% (adj.) of setpoint and return fan speed is lower than 85% (adj.) when AHU return fan status is On.\nThe above conditions to remain true for >30mins (adj.) 2 (adj.) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj.) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check if AHU return fan speed command is overridden between minimum speed and 85% on front end.\n2. Check for any mechanical issues/faults in return fan motor/VSD.\n3. Validate AHU return fan speed control logic in controller to ensure fan speed is commanded to minimum speed.\n4. Verify fan speed control design, return duct pressure setpoint, return duct pressure sensor location.");
s("name","raPressureHigherThanSPLowSpeed");
s("help2","AHU return duct static pressure is higher than setpoint by 20% (adj.) of setpoint and return fan speed is lower than 85% (adj.) when AHU return fan status is On.\nThe above conditions to remain true for >30mins (adj.) 2 (adj.) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj.) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check if AHU return fan speed command is overridden between minimum speed and 85% on front end.\n2. Check for any mechanical issues/faults in return fan motor/VSD.\n3. Validate AHU return fan speed control logic in controller to ensure fan speed is commanded to minimum speed.\n4. Verify fan speed control design, return duct pressure setpoint, return duct pressure sensor location.");
