y(d,"func:eaFlowLowerThanSPLowSpeed");
s("dis","EA Low Flow Rate with Fan Speed < 85%");
s("help","Exhaust Fan Flow Rate is lower than setpoint by 10% (adj) of setpoint and fan speed is lower than 85% (adj).\nThe above conditions to remain true for >30mins (adj) 2 (adj) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check if EF fan speed command is overridden between minimum speed and 85% on front end.\n2. Check for any mechanical issues/faults in exhaust fan motor/VSD.\n3. Validate EF fan speed control logic in controller to ensure fan speed is commanded to minimum speed.\n4. Verify fan speed control design, flow setpoint, flow sensor location.");
s("name","eaFlowLowerThanSPLowSpeed");
s("help2","Exhaust Fan Flow Rate is lower than setpoint by 10% (adj) of setpoint and fan speed is lower than 85% (adj).\nThe above conditions to remain true for >30mins (adj) 2 (adj) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check if EF fan speed command is overridden between minimum speed and 85% on front end.\n2. Check for any mechanical issues/faults in exhaust fan motor/VSD.\n3. Validate EF fan speed control logic in controller to ensure fan speed is commanded to minimum speed.\n4. Verify fan speed control design, flow setpoint, flow sensor location.");
