y(d,"func:mixedTempSensOutofRange");
s("dis","Mixed Air Temperature Sensor value out of limit");
s("ruleOn","mixed and air and temp and sensor");
s("param","(_,_,/*loLimit:*/6,/*hiLimit:*/35,/*minTime:*/30min,/*maxTime:*/60min,/*statuscheck:*/true,/*ruleWorkOrder:*/\"None\",/*freq:*/2,/*priority:*/\"Medium\",/*type:*/\"Operations\")");
s("param2","(_,_,/*loLimit:*/42,/*hiLimit:*/95,/*minTime:*/30min,/*maxTime:*/60min,/*statuscheck:*/true,/*ruleWorkOrder:*/\"None\",/*freq:*/2,/*priority:*/\"Medium\",/*type:*/\"Operations\")");
s("help","Mixed Air temperature sensor is higher than 35°C (adj) or lower than 6°C (adj) when equipment status is On.\n\nThe above conditions to remain true for >30mins (adj) 2 (adj) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check sensor for any faults/damage.\n2. Check sensor to controller cable/wire faults, loose connections.\n3. Verify voltage/current signals from sensor to controller terminals. Verify power supply to sensor.\n4. Check for any damage/faults in controller terminals.\n5. Validate the sensor point characteristics in controller software.\n6. Check manual overrides on front end/controller.");
s("name","mixedTempSensOutofRange");
s("help2","Mixed Air temperature sensor is higher than 95°F (adj) or lower than 42°F (adj) when equipment status is On.  The above conditions to remain true for >30mins (adj) 2 (adj) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check sensor for any faults/damage.\n2. Check sensor to controller cable/wire faults, loose connections.\n3. Verify voltage/current signals from sensor to controller terminals. Verify power supply to sensor.\n4. Check for any damage/faults in controller terminals.\n5. Validate the sensor point characteristics in controller software.\n6. Check manual overrides on front end/controller.");
y(d,"func:ruleManagement_reasonTableCleanup");
s("name","ruleManagement_reasonTableCleanup");
s(o,"Removes all invalid entries from the rule reason table from the passed in mod time onwards.\nThe mod time of all associated rules and assets is also checked to determine which entries\nshould be tested for cleanup. Eg/ If only an asset has changed in the system then all entries\nrelated to that asset will be tested.\n\nInvalid entries are classified as either of the following:\n- have an invalid ruleRef\n- have an invalid targetRef\n\nExample:\npre>\nruleManagement_reasonTableCleanup(dateTime(1970-01-01, 00:00))\n<pre");
