y(d,"func:mlOls");
s("name","mlOls");
s(o,"Create a training model for doing ordinary least-squares regression (OLS).\n\nBy default, Singular Value Decomposition (SVD) is used to fit the model.\nSet the 'qr' parameter to 'true' to use QR decomposition. QR is faster\nthan SVD, however, it cannot handle rank-deficient matrices. If you are\nusing QR and are getting errors, try switching back to SVD.\n\nWhen training this model there is **NO NEED** to include a constant\ncolumn of 1s for bias.\n\nThe following stats are available via `mlStats` once the model\nhas been trained.\n  - 'coeffs':  (Number[]) linear coefficients (without intercept)\n  - 'intercept'\n  - 'residuals'\n  - 'rss': residual sum of squares\n  - 'error': residual standard error\n  - 'df': degree-of-freedom of residual standard error\n  - 'r2': R-Squared statistic\n  - 'r2adj': Adjusted R-Squared statistic\n  - 'ftest': F-statistic of \"goodness-of-fit\"\n  - 'pvalue': p-value of \"goodnes-of-fit\"\n  - 'ttest': (Grid) The t-test of the coefficients (including intercept).\n  The first column is the coefficients, the second column is the standard\n  error of coefficients, the third column is the t-score of the hypothesis\n  test if the coefficient is zero, the fourth column is the p-values of\n  test. The last row is of intercept.\n");
