y(d,"func:hisWrite");
s("haystackApi","Write time series data to historian");
s("name","hisWrite");
s(o,"Asynchronously write the specified timestamp/value pairs to\nthe history.  The timestamps must match 'tz' of history.  If\nthe history has a 'unit' tag, then the items have either a null\nor matching unit.  Return future which may be used to track\nwhen write completes - the value of the future subject to change.\n\nThe data may be one of the following:\n  - Dict with 'ts' and 'val' tags; writes one pair to the history\n  - List of Dicts with 'ts' and 'val' tags; writes the list of\n    items to the history\n  - Grid where first column is 'ts' and second column (may be named\n    anything) is the values\n\nThe hisRec parameter may be:\n  - Ref of history to write to\n  - Rec of history to write to\n\nOptions:\n - 'noWarn': suppress out of order warning logging\n - 'forecast': set to marker to write as [forecast data]`ext-his::doc#forecast`\n\nSide effects:\n  - updates his rec tags hisSize, hisStart, etc\n  - clears context read cache\n\nSee `ext-his::doc#writing`\n");
