y(d,"func:lowPreheatTemp");
s("dis","Low Preheat Temperature");
s("help","AHU Preheat off coil/Mixed air temperature is less than 10degC (adj) and preheat valve is greater than 50% (adj) when AHU is On.\nThe above conditions to remain true for >30mins (adj) 2 (adj) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check if AHU Preheat valve is overridden to a position between 50% and 100% on front end.\n2. Check if Preheat valve is physically stuck. Check for any mechanical issues/faults in actuator, valve.\n3. Check and verify the voltage signals from controller to valve actuator.\n4. Validate AHU Preheat control logic in controller to ensure preheat valve is commanded to 100% (max position).\n5. Verify preheat control design, setpoints, preheat coil specificiations, sensor location.");
s("name","lowPreheatTemp");
s("help2","AHU Preheat off coil/Mixed air temperature is less than 50°F (adj) and preheat valve is greater than 50% (adj) when AHU is On.\nThe above conditions to remain true for >30mins (adj) 2 (adj) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check if AHU Preheat valve is overridden to a position between 50% and 100% on front end.\n2. Check if Preheat valve is physically stuck. Check for any mechanical issues/faults in actuator, valve.\n3. Check and verify the voltage signals from controller to valve actuator.\n4. Validate AHU Preheat control logic in controller to ensure preheat valve is commanded to 100% (max position).\n5. Verify preheat control design, setpoints, preheat coil specificiations, sensor location.");
