y(d,"func:znPressureLessThanSPLowSpeed");
s("dis","Low Room Differential Pressure with Exhaust Fan Speed <85%");
s("help","Room differential pressure is lower than setpoint by 20% (adj.) of setpoint and exhaust fan speed is lower than 85% (adj.).\nThe above conditions to remain true for >60mins (adj.) 2 (adj.) times or more in a day or >120mins (adj.) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check if exhaust fan speed command is overridden between minimum speed and 85% on front end.\n2. Check for any mechanical issues/faults in exhaust fan motor/VSD.\n3. Validate exhaust fan speed control logic in controller to ensure fan speed is commanded to minimum speed.\n4. Verify fan speed control design, exhaust duct pressure setpoint, exhaust duct pressure sensor location.");
