y(d,"func:vavZoneColdRhtOn_MinDmpPD");
s("dis","VAV Zone Cold when damper at min position & Reheat is ON");
s("help","VAV zone temp is less than setpoint by 5°C (adj.) when damper is at minimum position and Reheat valve is open >5% (adj.) or any Reheat stage is On and AHU Status is On in occupied mode.\nAssociated AHU discharge temperature is satisfied.\nThe above conditions were true for >60mins (adj.) (2 times or more in a day) or >120mins (adj.) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check if damper is physically stuck or manually overridden on front end.\n2. Check if damper is at design minimum position.\n3. Verify Reheat valve/stages point characteristics/configuration in controller.\n4. Verify VAV box damper point characteristics/configurations in controller & actuator voltage/power.\n5. Check sensor location or any external influence (Infiltration/Exfiltration).\n6. Check if Reheat Valve/Actuator/Stage relay is faulty.\n7. Verify zone temp SP, AHU duct static pressure SP, AHU discharge temp SP, Hot water supply temp SP (for Reheat Valves) is as per design.");
s("name","vavZoneColdRhtOn_MinDmpPD");
s("help2","VAV zone temp is less than setpoint by 5°F (adj.) when damper is at minimum position and Reheat valve is open >5% (adj.) or any Reheat stage is On and AHU Status is On in occupied mode. Associated AHU discharge temperature is satisfied. The above conditions were true for >60mins (adj.) (2 times or more in a day) or >120mins (adj.) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check if damper is physically stuck or manually overridden on front end.\n2. Check if damper is at design minimum position.\n3. Verify Reheat valve/stages point characteristics/configuration in controller.\n4. Verify VAV box damper point characteristics/configurations in controller & actuator voltage/power.\n5. Check sensor location or any external influence (Infiltration/Exfiltration).\n6. Check if Reheat Valve/Actuator/Stage relay is faulty.\n7. Verify zone temp SP, AHU duct static pressure SP, AHU discharge temp SP, Hot water supply temp SP (for Reheat Valves) is as per design.");
