s(o,"Calculate emissions for an equip, site, or ghgSource. The parameters:\n  - target: May be any target accepted by `toRec`.\n  - span (Span): Span to calculate the emissions for.\n\nThe 'opts' parameter is a Dict and supports the following options:\n - co2e (Marker): When set will return the Emissions calculation of the\n Carbon Dioxide Equivalent using the co2e emission factor if present or\n the sum of all configured Emissions using the configured Global Warming\n Potential of each Emission.\n - equivalent (Marker or Str): When set function will return Emissions\n calculations converted to equivalent estimated concrete values that may\n be easier to understand, such as the number of passenger vehicles driven\n per year.  When specified as a marker tag, all available equivalent\n calculations are returned.  A string value for one of the availble\n equivalent calculations can also be specified to return that individual\n value.\n - submeter (Marker): When set function will return Emissions calculation\n for submeters. By default, if an equip record has a meter tag than only\n Emissions calculations for siteMeters will be returned.\n\nReturns a Grid with emissions calculations.\n\nExample:\n   //Calculate individual emissions for lastMonth\n   ghgEmissions(@Equip, lastMonth)\n\n   //Calculate Carbon Dioxide Equivalent for lastMonth\n   ghgEmissions(@Site, lastMonth, {co2e})\n\n   //Calculate Equivalent Emission Values for lastMonth\n   ghgEmissions(@ghgSource, lastMonth, {equivalent})\n");
