s(o,"Convert a number to its string representation in the given radix (base).\nIf width is non-null, then leading zeroes are prepended to ensure the\nspecified width.\n\nExample:\n  6.toRadix(2) => \"110\"\n  255.toRadix(16, 4) => \"00ff\"\n");
y(d,"func:discreteEnumPeriods");
s("name","discreteEnumPeriods");
s(o,"Fold timestamp/enum Str value pairs into an encoded Str of discrete\nminutely intervals.  This rollup works very similar to `discretePeriods`\nwith the same Base64 encoding.  The difference is that instead of\noffset/duration pairs, the encoding is offset/ordinal pairs.  The\nordinal values map the position of each string value in the point's\n`enum` tag.  If a string value is not mapped by 'enum' then a value\nof 0xff (255) is used for the ordinal. If a string value is NA, then a\nvalue of 0xfff (4095) is used for the ordinal.\n\nAlso see `parseDiscreteEnumPeriods` and `haystack::Etc.discretePeriods`.\n");
s("foldOn","Str");
