s("help","AHU Zone/RA humidity is lower than setpoint by 10% (adj.) of humidity setpoint and Humidifier is greater than 10% (adj.) when AHU status is On.\nThe above conditions to remain true for >30mins (adj.) 2 (adj.) times or more in a day or >60mins (adj) once in a day to trigger the fault.\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Check if AHU Humidifier command is overridden to a position between 10% and 100% on front end.\n2. Check if humidifier valve is physically stuck. Check for any mechanical issues/faults in actuator, valve.\n3. Check and verify the voltage signals from controller to humidifier.\n4. Validate AHU humidity control logic in controller to ensure humidifier is commanded to 100% (max position).\n5. Verify humidity control design, humidity setpoint, sensor location.");
